Re: Why/How did this "に" get translated into "and"?
by Ongakuka » Sat 07.02.2011 10:05 am I'm pretty sure やさひく isn't classical Japanese, which leaves the only options beingA) it's a printing mistakeB) it's some kind of 方言I wouldn't rule out either, but it does sound weird so for now lets assume its a mistake.
なぜなら、おまえは・・・・・・人形だ
