Re: Why/How did this "に" get translated into "and"?
by chibola » Sat 07.02.2011 11:00 am Thank so much to everyone for their input. I think I'll just go with the printing error for the "yasashiku." Oh, and special thanks to hyperworm for telling me "ni" is also a list particle. I didn't know that at all. But... when would you use it? I mean, if you have "ya" already, why make "ni" a list particle, too? Just for variation?I appreciate all of you taking the time to answer! chibola
